[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":673},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F10\u002Fauto-deploy-hexo-articles\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F10\u002Fauto-deploy-hexo-articles\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F10\u002Fauto-deploy-hexo-articles\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F10\u002Fauto-deploy-hexo-articles\u002F":650,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F10\u002Fauto-deploy-hexo-articles\u002F":659},"\u002Fhexo\u002F20190910\u002F3668677278\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":635,"date":636,"description":19,"extension":637,"lang":638,"meta":639,"navigation":640,"path":641,"readingMinutes":642,"seo":643,"standalone":644,"stem":645,"tags":646,"tldr":647,"updated":636,"url":648,"__hash__":649},"content\u002Fen\u002FHexo\u002Fauto-deploy-hexo-articles.md","Auto-Deploying Hexo Articles","8727768663",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":626},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,34,42,46,57,77,90,96,104,112,118,121,127,130,136,139,145,149,156,161,171,176,179,185,188,194,198,201,207,214,219,228,233,248,253,259,266,272,275,281,288,294,300,304,311,317,320,556,562,568,571,577,580,586,589,595,599,622],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Deploying articles by hand has been getting old, so I'm switching Hexo deploy to fully automated.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"why-automate","Why automate",[17,25,26],{},"Hexo's compile time is slow — on lower-spec machines it can take over 2 minutes. And you have to keep the compile window open while it runs, like this ↓",[17,28,29],{},[30,31],"img",{"alt":32,"src":33},"Compiling","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FY9iTgsS.png",[17,35,36,37,41],{},"Auto-deploy fixes this — the CI tool watches your repo, and as soon as it sees a change, it compiles. No more keeping a window open to run ",[38,39,40],"code",{},"hexo d -g",".",[12,43,45],{"id":44},"sign-up-for-travis-ci","Sign up for Travis CI",[17,47,48,49,52,53,56],{},"Head to Travis CI's site. Two flavours: ",[38,50,51],{},".org"," (free) and ",[38,54,55],{},".com"," (commercial):",[58,59,60,70],"ul",{},[61,62,63],"li",{},[64,65,69],"a",{"href":66,"rel":67},"https:\u002F\u002Ftravis-ci.org\u002F",[68],"nofollow","Open-source",[61,71,72],{},[64,73,76],{"href":74,"rel":75},"https:\u002F\u002Ftravis-ci.com\u002F",[68],"Commercial",[17,78,79,80,84,85,89],{},"I'd recommend ",[64,81,83],{"href":66,"rel":82},[68],"the open-source version",", but it doesn't support private repos. If your project is private, you have to use ",[64,86,88],{"href":74,"rel":87},[68],"the commercial version",", which costs money — though their pricing page mentions the first 100 builds are free ↓",[17,91,92],{},[30,93],{"alt":94,"src":95},"First 100 free","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLcKOZ9S.png",[17,97,98,99,41],{},"Commercial pricing for reference: ",[64,100,103],{"href":101,"rel":102},"https:\u002F\u002Ftravis-ci.com\u002Fplans",[68],"Travis CI commercial plans",[17,105,106,107,111],{},"For this post I'll be using the ",[108,109,110],"strong",{},"commercial version",", so the open-source UI will look slightly different — but the flow is roughly the same. Let's get into it ↓",[17,113,114],{},[30,115],{"alt":116,"src":117},"Travis CI","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FeczHQ9G.png",[17,119,120],{},"Click \"Sign up with GitHub\" in the middle. It'll prompt for authorization ↓",[17,122,123],{},[30,124],{"alt":125,"src":126},"Authorize","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FdC0INND.png",[17,128,129],{},"GitHub usually asks for your password again ↓",[17,131,132],{},[30,133],{"alt":134,"src":135},"Password","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FQQhCCwV.png",[17,137,138],{},"Once registered you'll land on the Travis CI screen ↓",[17,140,141],{},[30,142],{"alt":143,"src":144},"Travis CI dashboard","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FldIa005.png",[12,146,148],{"id":147},"set-up-the-repository","Set up the repository",[17,150,151,152,155],{},"Now set up your Hexo source repo (note: not the static-pages repo). Click ",[108,153,154],{},"Activate"," ↓",[17,157,158],{},[30,159],{"alt":154,"src":160},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F3rgZh4d.png",[17,162,163,164,167,168,155],{},"Pick ",[108,165,166],{},"Only Select Repositories",", find your Hexo source, and click ",[108,169,170],{},"Activate & Install",[17,172,173],{},[30,174],{"alt":170,"src":175},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FZMfBqWc.png",[17,177,178],{},"Wait a moment ↓",[17,180,181],{},[30,182],{"alt":183,"src":184},"Loading","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FdeU7ABB.png",[17,186,187],{},"When you see this screen, you're set up ↓",[17,189,190],{},[30,191],{"alt":192,"src":193},"Done","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F8b31Gvs.png",[12,195,197],{"id":196},"get-set-the-github-token","Get & set the GitHub token",[17,199,200],{},"To deploy, you need a GitHub token. Click the top-right corner to open Settings ↓",[17,202,203],{},[30,204],{"alt":205,"src":206},"Settings","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F0MfNRCc.png",[17,208,209,210,213],{},"Click ",[108,211,212],{},"Developer settings"," in the left sidebar ↓",[17,215,216],{},[30,217],{"alt":212,"src":218},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FhsEsxQH.png",[17,220,209,221,224,225,155],{},[108,222,223],{},"Personal access tokens",", then ",[108,226,227],{},"Generate new token",[17,229,230],{},[30,231],{"alt":223,"src":232},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FantxFUO.png",[17,234,235,236,239,240,243,244,247],{},"For the token, I'd recommend putting ",[38,237,238],{},"Travis CI auto deploy"," in the Note field so you don't accidentally delete it later. Below, check ",[38,241,242],{},"public_repo"," (or the whole ",[38,245,246],{},"repo"," scope if you prefer) ↓",[17,249,250],{},[30,251],{"alt":238,"src":252},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fh04PXwj.png",[17,254,255,256,258],{},"After creating, your new token shows up in ",[108,257,223],{},". Copy it immediately — you won't see it again ↓",[17,260,261,262,265],{},"(",[108,263,264],{},"Important: this token is sensitive. Don't share it.",")",[17,267,268],{},[30,269],{"alt":270,"src":271},"Token","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F2bvSXpE.png",[17,273,274],{},"Back in Travis CI's Settings screen, click Setting ↓",[17,276,277],{},[30,278],{"alt":279,"src":280},"Setting","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FORA7J1V.png",[17,282,283,284,287],{},"Scroll down to ",[108,285,286],{},"Environment Variables",". Set the name and paste the token into VALUE, then click ADD ↓",[17,289,290,291,265],{},"(I'd suggest naming it ",[38,292,293],{},"GITHUB_TOKEN",[17,295,296],{},[30,297],{"alt":298,"src":299},"ADD","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FE9Befa4.png",[12,301,303],{"id":302},"add-the-travis-config","Add the Travis config",[17,305,306,307,310],{},"Create ",[38,308,309],{},".travis.yml"," in the root of your Hexo project ↓",[17,312,313],{},[30,314],{"alt":315,"src":316},"Travis config","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FUo5A6Ex.png",[17,318,319],{},"Contents ↓",[321,322,327],"pre",{"className":323,"code":324,"language":325,"meta":326,"style":326},"language-yml shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","# Set system language environment\nlanguage: node_js\n# Whether sudo is required\nsudo: false\n# Set node_js version\nnode_js:\n  - '10'\n# Cache settings\ncache:\n  apt: true\n  directories:\n      - node_modules # folder that doesn't change often\n# Branch to deploy from. Usually master.\nbranches:\n  only:\n    - master\n## Install Hexo-Cli\nbefore_script:\n  - npm install hexo-cli -g  # install Hexo\n# Clean cache and compile\nscript:\n  - hexo clean\n  - hexo generate\n## Deploy config\nafter_success:\n  - sed -i'' \"\u002F^ *repo\u002Fs~github\\.com~${GITHUB_TOKEN}@github.com~\" _config.yml\n  - hexo deploy\n","yml","",[38,328,329,338,353,359,371,377,386,395,401,409,420,428,440,446,454,462,471,477,485,496,502,510,518,526,532,540,548],{"__ignoreMap":326},[330,331,334],"span",{"class":332,"line":333},"li